**Page Object Model (POM):**
- Each page/component = a class encapsulating locators and actions
- Tests read in domain language: `loginPage.loginAs('user', 'pass')`
- Locator changes require 1 file change, not 50
- Anti-pattern: POM methods with assertions — keep pages as 'what you can do', not 'what you expect'

**Screenplay Pattern (SERENITY):**
- Actors have Abilities (can BrowseTheWeb, can CallAnApi)
- Tasks are reusable actions (PlaceOrder, LoginAs)
- Questions extract state for assertions
- Better than POM at scale — composable, no god-class pages

**Singleton for WebDriver:**
```java
public class DriverManager {
  private static ThreadLocal<WebDriver> driver = new ThreadLocal<>();
  public static WebDriver getDriver() { return driver.get(); }
  public static void setDriver(WebDriver d) { driver.set(d); }
}
```
ThreadLocal ensures parallel tests each have their own driver instance.

**Factory for multi-browser/mobile:**
```java
public class DriverFactory {
  public static WebDriver create(String type) {
    return switch(type) {
      case 'chrome' -> new ChromeDriver();
      case 'firefox' -> new FirefoxDriver();
      case 'mobile' -> new AppiumDriver(...);
    };
  }
}
```

**Common SDET live coding topics:**

**String manipulation:**
```java
// Reverse words in string
String reverseWords(String s) {
  return Arrays.stream(s.trim().split('\\s+'))
    .map(w -> new StringBuilder(w).reverse())
    .collect(Collectors.joining(' '));
}
```

**HashMap patterns:**
```java
// Find duplicate characters
Map<Character, Integer> freq = new HashMap<>();
for (char c : str.toCharArray()) {
  freq.merge(c, 1, Integer::sum);
}
freq.entrySet().stream()
  .filter(e -> e.getValue() > 1)
  .forEach(...);
```

**Array sorting for test data:**
```java
// Sort by multiple fields (test results)
testResults.sort(Comparator.comparing(TestResult::getStatus)
  .thenComparing(TestResult::getDuration));
```

**SDET-specific: Parse test log**
```python
import re
def parse_failures(log: str) -> list[str]:
  return re.findall(r'FAILED: (.+)', log)
```

**Live coding tips:**
- Think out loud — interviewer wants to see problem-solving process
- Start with brute force, then optimize
- Handle nulls and edge cases explicitly
- Write a helper test first to validate your solution
- Name variables clearly — readability > cleverness

